☸️ 2. Kubernetes Architecture
Master (Control Plane):
API Server → entry point
Scheduler → assigns pods
Controller Manager → maintains state
etcd → stores cluster data
Worker Nodes:
Kubelet → communicates with master
Container runtime (Docker/containerd)
Kube-proxy → networking

📈 3. Auto-scaling in Kubernetes
Yes — used HPA
Scales pods based on CPU/memory metrics
Improves performance during traffic spikes

⚖️ 4. HPA vs VPA
HPA → Scales number of pods
VPA → Adjusts CPU/memory of pod
HPA = horizontal scaling
VPA = vertical scaling

💥 5. When a Pod crashes
Kubernetes restarts container automatically
Based on restart policy
If continuous failure → CrashLoopBackOff
Logs help identify issue

🔍 6. Explore applications in cluster
kubectl get pods
kubectl get svc
kubectl describe pod
kubectl logs
Use labels/selectors

⚙️ 7. Terraform Modules
Reusable blocks of code
Example: VPC module, EC2 module
Improves maintainability and reusability

🧱 8. Sample Terraform EC2 Module
# modules/ec2/main.tf
resource "aws_instance" "this" {
  ami           = var.ami
  instance_type = var.instance_type

  tags = {
    Name = var.name
  }
}

# modules/ec2/variables.tf
variable "ami" {}
variable "instance_type" {}
variable "name" {}

# root main.tf
module "ec2" {
  source        = "./modules/ec2"
  ami           = "ami-123456"
  instance_type = "t2.micro"
  name          = "my-instance"
}

